提名名單后不久，多家媒体观察到主要奖项提名者连续第二年缺乏多样性<ref name="Variety 2016-01-14">{{cite news |last=Gray |first=Tim |url=http://variety.com/2016/biz/news/oscar-nominations-2016-diversity-white-1201674903/ |title=Academy Nominates All White Actors for Second Year in Row |work=Variety |publisher=Penske Media Corporation |date=2016-01-14 |accessdate=2016-01-18 |quote=Last year’s Oscar nominations drew howls of protests for their lack of diversity. This year, it’s even worse. |archive-date=2016-01-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117194332/http://variety.com/2016/biz/news/oscar-nominations-2016-diversity-white-1201674903/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Time 2016-01-14">{{cite news |last=Begley |first=Sarah |url=http://time.com/4180433/oscar-nominations-white-diversity-oscarssowhite/ |title=The Oscars Are Very White This Year—Again |work=Time |date=2016-01-14 |accessdate=2016-01-18 |archive-date=2016-01-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117233758/http://time.com/4180433/oscar-nominations-white-diversity-oscarssowhite/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Vanity Fair 2016-01-14">{{cite news |last=Hogan |first=Mike |url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2016/01/oscars-so-white-2016 |title=The Oscars Are Way Too White, Again |work=Vanity Fair |date=2016-01-14 |accessdate=2016-01-18 |archive-date=2016-01-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117094914/http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2016/01/oscars-so-white-2016 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/2016/01/14/oscar_snubs_that_hurt_the_academy_awards_still_arent_designed_for_anyone_who_isnt_white_straight_and_male/|script-title=en:Oscar snubs that hurt: The Academy Awards still aren’t designed for anyone who isn’t white, straight, and male|work=Salon|first=Nico|last=Lang|date=2016-01-14|accessdate=2016-01-20|archive-date=2016-01-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160119061314/http://www.salon.com/2016/01/14/oscar_snubs_that_hurt_the_academy_awards_still_arent_designed_for_anyone_who_isnt_white_straight_and_male/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。随后学院主席谢丽尔·布恩·艾萨克斯（Cheryl Boone Isaacs）表示：

{{cquote|当然，我很失望，但不能带走它們（提名电影）的伟大。这是电影界最伟大的一年……然而，我们没有停步……我们正在前行，用說話和行动方式。这不仅需要在学院内部发生，还关系到整个电影界<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.rollingstone.com/movies/news/academy-president-addresses-lack-of-oscar-diversity-20160114 | title=Academy President Addresses Lack of Oscar Diversity | work=Rolling Stone |date=2016-01-15 | accessdate=2016-01-15|first=Althea|last= Legaspi}}</ref>。}}

艾萨克斯表示，学院正采取“重大举措”来改变其成员组成，并會多样化“性别、种族、民族和性取向”领域<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-academy-president-cheryl-boone-857016|title=Academy President Issues Lengthy Statement on Lack of Oscars Diversity|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2016-01-18|accessdate=2016-01-20|archive-date=2016-01-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160119215910/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-academy-president-cheryl-boone-857016|dead-url=no}}</ref>。之後学院发表声明，宣布采取措施改变投票权和成员规则，包括增加女性和少数族裔成员数量、更改除非获得或被提名奥斯卡奖，必須在演藝圈工作30年的终生投票权利<ref>{{cite news| url = http://oscar.go.com/news/oscar-news/the-academy-introduces-plan-to-improve-oscar-diversity| title = The Academy Introduces Plan to Improve Oscar Diversity| first = Sarah| last = Huggins| publisher = Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences| date = 2016-01-26| accessdate = 2016-01-28| archive-date = 2016-01-26| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160126222645/http://oscar.go.com/news/oscar-news/the-academy-introduces-plan-to-improve-oscar-diversity| dead-url = no}}</ref>。艾萨克斯表示，“学院将会掀起潮流，不需要等待整个行业赶上来，这些措施会有立竿见影之效，开始显著改变我们成员的形成过程<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.oscars.org/news/academy-takes-historic-action-increase-diversity | title = Lifetime voting rights reframed; new governor seats added and committees restructured - Goal to double number of diverse members by 2020 | publisher = Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences | date = 2016-01-22 | accessdate = 2016-01-22 | archive-date = 2016-01-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160123094038/http://www.oscars.org/news/academy-takes-historic-action-increase-diversity | dead-url = no }}</ref>。”学院还會新增三名理事席位，任期三年，由学院主席提名并经董事会确认<ref>{{cite news | url = http://variety.com/2016/film/awards/oscars-diversity-academy-emergency-meeting-1201685630/ | title = Academy Overhauls Membership, Voting Rules to Promote Oscar Diversity | first = Tim | last = Gray | work = Variety | accessdate = 2016-01-22 | archive-date = 2016-01-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160122215745/http://variety.com/2016/film/awards/oscars-diversity-academy-emergency-meeting-1201685630/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。学院还向行政和董事会成员新增对成员和管理层构成作关键决策的职务<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.theverge.com/2016/1/22/10816010/academy-award-voters-diversity-plan-2020-oscars | title = The Academy announces goal to 'double number of diverse members' after Oscar backlash | first = Jamieson | last = Cox | work = The Verge | accessdate = 2016-01-22 | archive-date = 2016-01-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160123214241/http://www.theverge.com/2016/1/22/10816010/academy-award-voters-diversity-plan-2020-oscars | dead-url = no }}</ref>。然而，学院的行动还包括撤走演员[[比尔·穆米|比尔·穆米]]和获奖编剧帕特里夏·雷斯尼克（{{lang|en|Patricia Resnick}}）等目前未在行业内工作的学院成员的会员权力。雷斯尼克表示“用年龄歧视换取性别歧视和种族歧视不是答案。”<ref name="guest"/><ref>{{cite news| title=Gay Female Oscar Voter to Academy: Don't Kick Me out "to Help You Deal With a Publicity Nightmare| url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/gay-female-oscar-voter-academy-860236| work=The Hollywood Reporter| date=2016-01-28| accessdate=2016-03-19| archive-date=2016-03-20| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320071305/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/gay-female-oscar-voter-academy-860236| dead-url=no}}</ref>。

