</div>{{SquoteF}}

[[迈克尔·凯恩|迈克尔·凯恩]]、[[艾斯·库伯|艾斯·库伯]]、[[夏洛特·兰普林|夏洛特·兰普林]]、[[乌比·戈德堡|乌比·戈德堡]]、{{le|佩内洛普·安·米勒|Penelope Ann Miller}}、[[海伦·米伦|海伦·米伦]]和{{le|杰拉尔德·R·莫伦|Gerald R. Molen}}则为奥斯卡辩护，表示提名基于表现和优点，而非种族<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/viola-davis-diversity-oscars-are-857858|title=Viola Davis on Diversity: "Oscars Are a Symptom of a Much Greater Issue"|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2016-01-21|accessdate=2016-02-04|archive-date=2016-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202062949/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/viola-davis-diversity-oscars-are-857858|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2016/01/22/world/europe/ap-eu-oscars-diversity-rampling.html|title=Charlotte Rampling Clarifies Controversial Diversity Remarks|work=The New York Times|date=2016-01-22|accessdate=2016-02-04|archive-date=2016-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126015335/http://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2016/01/22/world/europe/ap-eu-oscars-diversity-rampling.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscar-winning-producer-denounces-spoiled-858207|title=Oscar-Winning Producer Denounces "Spoiled Brats" Crying "Racism"|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2016-01-22|accessdate=2016-02-04|archive-date=2016-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160406033830/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscar-winning-producer-denounces-spoiled-858207|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="guest">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/topic/oscar-voter-guest-columns|title=Oscar Voter Guest Columns|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=2016-02-04|archive-date=2016-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205002419/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/topic/oscar-voter-guest-columns|dead-url=no}}</ref>。迈克尔·凯恩表示：“最后你不能以一个演员是黑人为由而不投票给他。你不能说‘我想把票投给他，虽然他不是很优秀，但他是个黑人，所以我会投他<ref>{{cite web|script-title=en:Michael Caine on Oscars: ‘You Can’t Vote for an Actor Because He’s Black’|url=http://variety.com/2016/film/news/michael-caine-oscars-black-actors-voting-1201686240/|work=Variety|date=2016-01-22|accessdate=2016-02-04|archive-date=2016-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205080922/http://variety.com/2016/film/news/michael-caine-oscars-black-actors-voting-1201686240/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”热门传记电影《冲出康普顿》制作人艾斯·库伯表示“这就像哭诉你的蛋糕不够冰，只会招人笑话<ref>{{cite web|last=Lewis|first=Hilary|title=Ice Cube on Oscars: 'You Can't Boycott Something That You Never Went To Anyway'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/oscars/6851680/ice-cube-straight-outta-compton-oscars-boycott-interview|work=Billboard|date=2016-01-22|accessdate=2016-02-04|archive-date=2016-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202074257/http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/oscars/6851680/ice-cube-straight-outta-compton-oscars-boycott-interview|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”佩内洛普·安·米勒回应批评时指出“我给几个黑人表演者投了票，但我很遗憾他们没有入选。拿这件事暗指我们都是种族主义者是很让人反感的。我不希望被归类为种族主义者，因为我肯定不是，况且我支持并受益于这个行业的黑人人才。这只不过是非常有竞争性的一年<ref>{{cite web|last=Feinberg|first=Scott|title=Academy Members Defend Their Oscar Votes: "To Imply We Are Racists Is Extremely Offensive"|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/oscarssowhite-academy-members-defend-oscar-857416|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2016-01-20|accessdate=2015-01-29|archive-date=2016-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160120164715/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/oscarssowhite-academy-members-defend-oscar-857416|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”奥斯卡奖得主、前主持人乌比·戈德堡为学院辩护时指出：“问题不在于学院。即便你将黑人、拉丁裔和亚裔成员填满学院，如果其中没有一个人要在电视上投票，你不会得到你想要的结果。我赢过一次，所以这算不上那种种族主义者。不管怎么说我是黑人<ref>{{cite web|title=From Michael Caine to Ice Cube: the best quotes against the entitled brats boycotting the Oscars|url=http://www.therebel.media/from_michael_caine_to_ice_cube_the_best_quotes_against_the_entitled_brats_boycotting_the_oscars|publisher=The Rebel Media|date=2016-01-26|accessdate=2016-01-29|archive-date=2016-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160130121639/http://www.therebel.media/from_michael_caine_to_ice_cube_the_best_quotes_against_the_entitled_brats_boycotting_the_oscars|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”制片人杰拉尔德·R·莫伦称抵制的想法“荒谬”，表示“除了那些制造问题的人，不存在有种族主义者”，并补充称“采用这种丑陋的方式表达抱怨的那种人最糟糕”<ref>{{cite web|title=Oscar boycott call drives wedge in Hollywood|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2016/01/23/oscar-boycott-call-drives-wedge-in-hollywood/|publisher=Fox News Channel|accessdate=2016-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160215135709/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2016/01/23/oscar-boycott-call-drives-wedge-in-hollywood/|archive-date=2016-02-15|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。奥斯卡得奖演员海伦·米伦为学院辩护时指出攻击组织“不公平”：“今年它只是用不好的方式放大了。”米伦提到[[Netflix|Netflix]]电影《[[无境之兽|无境之兽]]》的演員[[伊德瑞斯·艾尔巴|伊德瑞斯·艾尔巴]]曾被提名，但“因为没有足够多的人看过或希望看一部关于童子兵的电影”而落选。米伦指出问题出在行业，“电影被提名到奥斯卡前发生了什么？要制作什么类型的电影？选角和编剧要用什么方法？这些事情比谁拿着奥斯卡奖杯站上舞台更有影响力<ref>{{cite web|last1=Oswald|first1=Anjelica|title=Helen Mirren says it's 'unfair' to criticize the Oscars for nominating only white actors|url=http://finance.yahoo.com/news/helen-mirren-says-unfair-criticize-182655455.html|publisher=Yahoo! Finance|accessdate=2016-02-12|archive-date=2016-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205091530/http://finance.yahoo.com/news/helen-mirren-says-unfair-criticize-182655455.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”《[[新鲜王子妙事多|新鲜王子妙事多]]》前演员{{le|珍妮特·休伯特|Janet Hubert}}批评贾达·萍克特·史密斯发Facebook视频呼吁黑人演员“站在我们一边”，而不去核实奥斯卡名单<ref>{{cite web|last1=Johnson|first1=Craig|title=Oscarssowhite controversy shakes Hollywood|url=http://www.hlntv.com/articles/2016/01/20/oscars-so-white-debate-shakes-hollywood|publisher=HLNtv.com|accessdate=2016-02-10|archive-date=2016-02-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160217222046/http://www.hlntv.com/articles/2016/01/20/oscars-so-white-debate-shakes-hollywood|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2月下旬，《[[奎迪|奎迪]]》导演[[莱恩·库格勒|莱恩·库格勒]]和《[[塞尔玛游行|塞尔玛游行]]》导演[[阿娃·杜威内|阿娃·杜威内]]宣布将在2月28日奥斯卡颁奖典礼当日举办慈善活动，解决密歇根州弗林特的用水危机。众多奥斯卡提名名单“太白”的著名批评者决定推掉典礼参加#JusticeForFlint活动，而这被广泛认为是那些感到失望甚至抵制奥斯卡颁奖典礼人士转移视线的活动<ref>{{cite web |first=Crystal |last=Bell |title=If you're tired of watching white actors accept Oscars, Ryan Coogler is hosting something more important |publisher=MTV News |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2744224/ryan-coogler-justice-for-flint-oscars/ |date=2016-02-23 |accessdate=2016-02-28 |archive-date=2016-02-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160227162308/http://www.mtv.com/news/2744224/ryan-coogler-justice-for-flint-oscars/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 亚洲人玩笑话争议 ===
虽然主持人克里斯·洛克的主持表现获得多数人的好评，但他后来因和[[沙查·巴隆·科恩|沙查·巴隆·科恩]]在舞台上拿亚洲人的刻板形象和好战性格开玩笑而受到批评。节目期间，洛克带着三名冒充会计师的亚裔孩子走上舞台，表示“他们是最敬业、细心和勤奋的代表……有请明珠（{{lang|en|Ming Zhu}}）、保灵（{{lang|en|Bao Ling}}）和大卫·莫斯科维茨（{{lang|en|David Moskowitz}}）”。他继续说道，“如果有人被这个笑话困扰到了，只管用你那也是由这些孩子生产的手机发推文就可以了<ref name=wapost>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2016/02/29/the-oscars-were-all-about-diversity-but-people-hated-that-asian-joke/|title=If the Oscars were all about diversity, why the crude Asian joke?|work=The Washington Post|accessdate=2016-03-19|archive-date=2016-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323085844/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2016/02/29/the-oscars-were-all-about-diversity-but-people-hated-that-asian-joke/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

此外，以阿里G身份与[[奥利维亚·维尔德|奥利维亚·维尔德]]一同颁奖的[[沙查·巴隆·科恩|巴隆·科恩]]表示：“那些拿着卑微的越南盾薪水、兢兢业业、细心且勤奋的-{小黄人}-怎能没有奥斯卡奖。你不知道，这才是小黄人。”Slate的刘罗文指出了这个针对亚洲人的双关语笑话<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/browbeat/2016/02/29/why_chris_rock_and_ali_g_s_racist_asian_jokes_at_the_oscars_were_such_a.html|title=Why Chris Rock's Asian Joke Was Such a Disappointment.|work=Slate.com|author=Liu, Lowen|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229181927/http://www.slate.com/blogs/browbeat/2016/02/29/why_chris_rock_and_ali_g_s_racist_asian_jokes_at_the_oscars_were_such_a.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。拜伦·科恩的妻子、演员艾拉·费雪在他登台前帮他穿上角色的服装。她表示活动制作人曾明确授权他以其饰演的任何角色亮相，但她表示碰到洛克后拜伦的想法大胆了起来，这让他對执行這计划有了底气<ref name="VultureCohen">{{cite web|last1=Lockett|first1=Dee|last2=Fitz-Gerald|first2=Sean|script-title=en:Sacha Baron Cohen Wasn’t Allowed to Do Ali G at the Oscars, So Isla Fisher Helped Him Slip Into the Costume Right Before Going On|url=http://www.vulture.com/2016/02/sacha-baron-cohens-ali-g-crashed-the-oscars.html|website=Vulture.com|publisher=Vulture|accessdate=2016-03-19|archive-date=2016-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320152401/http://www.vulture.com/2016/02/sacha-baron-cohens-ali-g-crashed-the-oscars.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

除了公众的批评，尤其是在网上<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/child-labor-isn-t-funny-twitter-reacts-oscars-asian-joke-n527731|author=Lee, Traci G.|title=Oscars 2016: Twitter Reacts to 'Asian Joke' at Academy Awards|work=NBC News|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229100655/http://www.nbcnews.com/news/asian-america/child-labor-isn-t-funny-twitter-reacts-oscars-asian-joke-n527731|dead-url=no}}</ref>，笑话还被《[[GQ|GQ]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gq.com/story/chris-rock-asian-joke-oscars|title=Why Chris Rock's Awkward Oscars Joke About Asian People Fell Flat|author=Gayomali, Chris|work=GQ|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301104657/http://www.gq.com/story/chris-rock-asian-joke-oscars|dead-url=no}}</ref>、《[[好莱坞报道者|好莱坞报道者]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-why-make-cheap-jokes-871623|title=Oscars: Why Make Cheap Jokes at the Expense of Asians?|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301014858/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-why-make-cheap-jokes-871623|dead-url=no}}</ref>、《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/01/movies/chris-rocks-asian-joke-at-oscars-provokes-backlash.html?smid=fb-nytimes&smtyp=cur|title=Chris Rock's Asian Joke at Oscars Provokes Backlash|work=The New York Times|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303021849/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/01/movies/chris-rocks-asian-joke-at-oscars-provokes-backlash.html?smid=fb-nytimes&smtyp=cur|dead-url=no}}</ref>和《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》批评<ref name=wapost/>。《华盛顿邮报》的杰西卡·康特雷拉（{{lang|en|Jessica Contrera}}）指出：“缺乏多样性中再有缺乏多样性。最为明显的是洛克将三名亚裔儿童领到台上，称之为金融公司[[普华永道|普华永道]]的‘银行家’<ref name=wapost/>。”《[[初来乍到|初来乍到]]》演员[[吴恬敏|吴恬敏]]和篮球运动员[[林书豪|林书豪]]也谈到了笑话，前者表示“把小孩放在舞台上，沒有台詞，充當种族主义笑话的對象，非常以简释繁、噁心。”后者在Twitter上称他厌倦了人們總是認為攻擊亞洲人沒什麼大不了<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jeremy-lin-slams-oscars-host-871641|title=Jeremy Lin Slams Chris Rock's Asian Jokes|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301062029/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jeremy-lin-slams-oscars-host-871641|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2016年3月9日，由台湾著名导演[[李安|李安]]、著名美籍日裔演员[[乔治·武井|乔治·武井]]、美籍华裔纪录片导演[[楊紫燁|楊紫燁]]等25位亚裔美国电影艺术与科学学院成员美籍华裔电影人以及美籍华裔电影人[[曾奕田|曾奕田]]、迪士尼动画导演{{le|唐·霍尔|Don Hall (filmmaker)}}等原美国电影艺术与科学学院成员联名向学院发出抗议信<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/ang-lee-george-takei-25-875772 |title=Ang Lee, George Takei Among 25 Academy Members Protesting Oscars' Asian Jokes |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=2016-03-15 |accessdate=2016-03-16 |archive-date=2016-06-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624232721/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/race/ang-lee-george-takei-25-875772 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。最终学院发表公开声明正式致歉<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/03/16/470722236/academys-apology-for-asian-jokes-at-oscars-falls-flat |title=Academy's Apology For Asian Jokes At Oscars Falls Flat |work=NPR |date=2016-03-16 |accessdate=2016-03-19 |archive-date=2016-03-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319014648/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2016/03/16/470722236/academys-apology-for-asian-jokes-at-oscars-falls-flat |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 专业评价和收视率 ===
节目获得媒体褒贬不一的评价。媒体普遍称赞主持人克里斯·洛克出色地处理了“多样性”问题。《[[洛杉矶时报|洛杉矶时报]]》电视评论员玛丽·麦克纳马拉（{{lang|en|Mary McNamara}}）表示：“洛克的奥斯卡制造了电视节目史上最强大的时刻”，认为他诚实回答了“好莱坞遍地种族主义者”的问题，“大胆且卓有成效”。她总结道，“转移了几年的话题后，今年的奥斯卡作出了行动。可以肯定的是，结果喜忧参半。洛克没能融入他一贯的愤慨和人性的平衡<ref>{{cite web|title=Chris Rock's hot mess of an Oscars show: powerful, confounding, possibly revolutionary|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/la-et-mn-oscars-tv-review-20160229-column.html|work=Mary McNamara|publisher=''Los Angeles Times''|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-03-01|archive-date=2016-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229222059/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/la-et-mn-oscars-tv-review-20160229-column.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》作家詹姆斯·泼尼沃齐克（{{lang|en|James Poniewozik}}）评论称“有了克里斯·洛克，奥斯卡找到了主持人和主题的幸运对子”，并表示洛克“他的表现为行业仍试着了解的事物做了示范，那就是给合适的人合适的机会，你可以同时实现包容性和娱乐性<ref>{{cite web|title=With Chris Rock, the Oscars Find a Lucky Pairing of Host and Subject|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/29/movies/chris-rock-oscars-review.html|work=Robert Bianco|publisher=''The New York Times''|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-03-01|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301044131/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/29/movies/chris-rock-oscars-review.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”《[[综艺_(杂志)|综艺]]》首席电视评论员布莱恩·洛瑞（{{lang|en|Brian Lowry}}）写道：“满足了逐步增强的过高期望值，克里斯·洛克出色地用开场独白穿针引线<ref>{{cite web|title=The 88th Annual Academy Awards: TV Review|url=http://variety.com/2016/tv/reviews/oscars-2016-review-chris-rock-academy-awards-leonardo-dicaprio-spotlight-oscarssowhite-1201716087/|work=Brian Lowry|publisher=Variety|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-03-01|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301092207/http://variety.com/2016/tv/reviews/oscars-2016-review-chris-rock-academy-awards-leonardo-dicaprio-spotlight-oscarssowhite-1201716087/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”《[[时代_(杂志)|时代]]》的丹尼尔·达达里奥（{{lang|en|Daniel D’Addario}}）称赞克里斯的主持表现，表示：“凭借尖酸刻薄的幽默和无拘无束的不可预测性，今年的奥斯卡是看上去不同寻常得满意的一届。”<ref>{{cite news|last1=D'Addario|first1=Daniel|title=Review: Chris Rock Anchors the Most Weirdly Successful Oscar Broadcast in Years|url=http://time.com/4240722/oscars-2016-review-chris-rock/|accessdate=2016-02-29|work=Time|date=2016-02-29|archive-date=2016-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229125721/http://time.com/4240722/oscars-2016-review-chris-rock/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。《[[今日美国|今日美国]]》的罗伯特·比安科（{{lang|en|Robert Bianco}}）称“洛克尖锐而坦率的談論奥斯卡和人种”，称典礼“搞笑、尖锐且咄咄逼人<ref>{{cite web|title=Rock pointedly tackles Oscars, and race|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2016/02/29/oscars-academy-awards-show-review/81075374/|work=Robert Bianco|publisher=''USA Today''|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-03-01|archive-date=2016-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229180830/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2016/02/29/oscars-academy-awards-show-review/81075374/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

然而，也有评论员对洛克的主持更持怀疑态度。公民权活动家{{le|肖恩·金|Shaun King (activist)}}在《[[纽约每日新闻|纽约每日新闻]]》严厉批评了洛克的主持表现和独白，称它“令人反感、不舒服，就是低级错误。”他进一步表示：“我一直在等他说些什么，说些有逻辑意义的东西，但它很快便演变成乱码般的不合逻辑胡言乱语<ref>{{cite web|title=Chris Rock Oscars opener dropped the ball and lynching jokes went over the line no matter how tough a spot it was|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/oscars/king-chris-rock-oscar-opener-lynching-jokes-article-1.2547017|work=Shaun King|publisher=''New York Daily News''|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-03-01|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301003627/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/oscars/king-chris-rock-oscar-opener-lynching-jokes-article-1.2547017|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”《好莱坞报道者》的丹尼尔·芬恩伯格（{{lang|en|Daniel Fienberg}}）打趣道：“克里斯·洛克开创了一档有重要话要说的电视节目，但仍让人感到无穷无尽。”此外，他还称典礼“塞得过满”且“又长又臭”<ref>{{cite web|title=The 88th Annual Academy Awards: TV Review|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/chris-rock-hosted-oscars-2016-871255|work=Daniel Fienberg|publisher=''The Hollywood Reporter''|date=2016-02-28|accessdate=2016-03-01|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301011915/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/chris-rock-hosted-oscars-2016-871255|dead-url=no}}</ref>。《时代》的金顺姬（{{lang|en|Grace Ji-Sun Kim}}）则评价洛克的开场白道：“克里斯·洛克应该知道种族主义不是黑白配，”并认为“如果我们要征服种族主义，我们必须承认这不是二元论<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ji-Sun Kim|first1=Grace|title=Chris Rock Should Know That Racism Isn’t Black and White|url=http://time.com/4240722/oscars-2016-review-chris-rock/|accessdate=2016-02-29|work=Time|date=2016-03-01|archive-date=2016-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229125721/http://time.com/4240722/oscars-2016-review-chris-rock/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”《[[圣何塞信使报|圣何塞信-{}-使报]]》评论员托尼·希克斯（{{lang|en|Tony Hicks}}）表示：“学院不應讓克里斯·洛克擔任奥斯卡主持人，他用那种肤色的人不會在好莱坞获得公平机会的謬誤，過份地扼杀周日晚上的奥斯卡頒獎禮的時間<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hicks|first1=Tony|title=Chris Rock could've done much better|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/tony-hicks/ci_29577180/academy-awards-chris-rock-couldve-done-much-better|accessdate=2016-02-29|work=San Jose Mercury|date=2016-03-01|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301095355/http://www.mercurynews.com/tony-hicks/ci_29577180/academy-awards-chris-rock-couldve-done-much-better|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

美国广播公司在美国的转播吸引3430万名观众全程观看<ref name="OscarRatingsTBN"/>，较全年典礼减少4%<ref>{{cite web|title=TV Ratings: Oscars Drop to Near All-Time Low With 34.3 Million Viewers|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/oscar-ratings-drop-low-343-871078|work=Michael O'Connell|publisher=Hollywood Reporter|date=2016-02-29|accessdate=2016-03-01|archive-date=2016-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160229215626/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/oscar-ratings-drop-low-343-871078|dead-url=no}}</ref>。电视转播还录得比去年典礼低的尼尔森收视率，有23.46%的家庭观看典礼，占总收视份额37%<ref name="OscarNielsenratings"/>。此外节目在18-49岁年龄段观众中录得较低的收视率，为10.5%，占总份额31%<ref>{{cite web|title=Oscar Ratings: Return Of Chris Rock Sees Show Hit 8-Year Low|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/03/01/sunday-final-ratings-feb-28-2016/|work=Rick Porter|publisher=tvbythenumbers|date=2016-03-01|accessdate=2016-03-04|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304055625/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/03/01/sunday-final-ratings-feb-28-2016/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。这是自2008年举办的[[第80届奥斯卡金像奖|第80届典礼]]以来收视率最低的一届<ref>{{cite web|title=Oscars TV Ratings Take a Nosedive, Hitting an 8-Year Low|url=http://fortune.com/2016/02/29/oscars-2016-tv-ratings-low/|work=Tom Huddleston, Jr.|publisher=Fortune|date=2016-02-29|accessdate=2016-03-01|archive-date=2016-03-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160302063032/http://fortune.com/2016/02/29/oscars-2016-tv-ratings-low/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

